OL,6,FButterflies are indicators of the
OL,7,Fhealth of our natural environment and
OL,8,Fcampaigners say it's never been more
OL,9,Fimportant to understand how these
OL,10,Fspecies are responding to the changing
OL,11,Fclimate and to take action to protect
OL,12,Fthem.
OL,14,FAnyone can take part by spending 15
OL,15,Fminutes outside and recording the
OL,16,Fnumber and type of butterflies they
OL,17,Fsee.
OL,19,FThe data is then analysed by
OL,20,Fscientists to help with conservation
OL,21,Fefforts.
